PRINCESS Charlotte will be christened next month, the Royal Family today revealed.&nbsp;A service will take place at St Mary Magdalene Church in Sandringham.Princess Charlotte Elizabeth Diana was born May 2.A statement from Kensington Palace read: &quot;The Duke and Duchess of Cambridge are pleased to announce the christening of Princess Charlotte will take place on Sunday July 5.&quot;Princess Charlotte will be christened by The Archbishop of Canterbury at JustinWelby at St Mary Magdalene Church in Sandringham.&quot;